body: The error seems not related to TRT. If you remove the option --use_tensorrt, will the compilation for CUDA pass?

Facing the same error without compiling tensorrt. build command used:

.\build.bat --config Debug --build_shared_lib --parallel --enable_training --use_cuda --cudnn_home "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.2" --cuda_home "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.2" --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019"

I tried it without --use_tensorrt and got the same error.

.\build.bat --parallel --config Release --build_wheel --cuda_version 11.0 --cudnn_home "C:\cuDNN\cudnn-11.0-windows-x64-v8.0.5.39\cuda" --cuda_home "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.0" --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019" --update --build

[resize_impl.cu257113780.deps.txt](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/6104568/resize_impl.cu257113780.deps.txt)
from the deps file I found, it appears that the MSVC header files are on the top, so the ceil() floor() calls are translated to windows SDK functions. But they should be cuda functions. 

is this a build.py script error?

1. It worked for me without any issue. I checked my environment. I have VS 16.7 + MSVC toolset v14.27.
2. I upgraded to VS 16.9, and can repo this issue. For VS 16.9 the default VC toolset is 14.28. So I re-installed MSVC V142 - VS 2019 C++ X64/X86 build tools (v14.27). It worked after force the toolset version to 14.27 by setting --msvc_toolset=14.27 in build command.
Please install MSVC toolset v14.27:
in Apps & Features -> find Microsoft Visual Studio Installer -> click Modify -> Choose 2019 Modify if you have multiple version -> Individual Components -> MSVC V142 - VS 2019 C++ X64/X86 build tools (v14.27), check it and install
 in your build command add: --msvc_toolset=14.27
We will look it further to see whether it's an issue with VC toolset or nvcc

issue.title: [1.6.0] Compilation error on Visual Studio 2019 16.10.0 / CUDA 11.1

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
Compiling onnxruntime from source with CMake stopped working after an update of Visual Studio 2019.
It compiles fine on the current Visual Studio 2017.
This is not a duplicate of #7562 nor #6927 as we do not build with TensorRT support (the code is not even checked out).

**Urgency**
None

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution: Windows Server 2019
- ONNX Runtime installed from: source
- ONNX Runtime version: 1.6.0
- Python version: Not built.
- Visual Studio version (if applicable): Visual Studio 2019 16.10.0
- CUDA/cuDNN version: 11.1.1 / 8.0.5.39

**To Reproduce**
The CMake call looks roughly like this:
```
cmake -G Visual Studio 16 2019 -A x64 -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE:STRING=Release -DBUILD_TYPE:STRING=Release -DBUILD_EXAMPLES:BOOL=OFF 
-DCMAKE_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBILITY:STRING=2.4 -DCMAKE_VERBOSE_MAKEFILE:BOOL=ON -DBUILD_TESTS:BOOL=OFF -DBUILD_TESTING:BOOL=OFF -DCMAKE_CXX_STANDARD:STRING=11 
-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_UNIT_TESTS=OFF -Donnxruntime_DEV_MODE=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_FEATURIZERS=OFF 
-Donnxruntime_ENABLE_PYTHON=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_OPENBLAS=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_DNNL=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_MKLML=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_NGRAPH=OFF 
-Donnxruntime_USE_OPENVINO=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_NNAPI_DNNLIBRARY=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_NNAPI_BUILTIN=OFF -Donnxruntime_ENABLE_MICROSOFT_INTERNAL=OFF 
-Donnxruntime_DISABLE_CONTRIB_OPS=OFF -Donnxruntime_MSVC_STATIC_RUNTIME=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_TELEMETRY=OFF -Donnxruntime_ENABLE_LTO=OFF 
-Donnxruntime_BUILD_BENCHMARKS=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_FULL_PROTOBUF=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_FOR_NATIVE_MACHINE=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_SHARED_LIB=ON 
-Donnxruntime_USE_EIGEN_FOR_BLAS=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_OPENMP=ON -Donnxruntime_ARMNN_RELU_USE_CPU=ON -Donnxruntime_ARMNN_BN_USE_CPU=ON 
-Donnxruntime_ENABLE_TRAINING=OFF -Donnxruntime_PREFER_SYSTEM_LIB=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_CUDA:BOOL=ON
-DCUDA_TOOLKIT_ROOT_DIR:PATH=C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.1 
-Donnxruntime_CUDA_HOME:PATH=C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.1 
-Donnxruntime_CUDNN_HOME:PATH=C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.1 
-T host=x64 H:/dev/Sources/onnxruntime/cmake
```

**Expected behavior**
Compilation should continue to work.

**Additional context**
Compilation errors similar to these now appear:
```
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign_impl.cu(131): error : calling a __host__ function("__ceilf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::RoIAlignForward<float> ") is not allowed
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign_impl.cu(131): error : identifier "__ceilf" is undefined in device code
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign_impl.cu(134): error : calling a __host__ function("__ceilf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::RoIAlignForward<float> ") is not allowed
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign_impl.cu(134): error : identifier "__ceilf" is undefined in device code
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : calling a __host__ function("__floorf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::_ResizeCubicCoordinateMapping<float> ") is not allowed
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : identifier "__floorf" is undefined in device code
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : calling a __host__ function("__floorf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::_ResizeCubicCoordinateMapping<double> ") is not allowed
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : identifier "__floorf" is undefined in device code
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : calling a __host__ function("__floorf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::_ResizeCubicCoordinateMapping<    ::__half> ") is not allowed
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : identifier "__floorf" is undefined in device code
.../onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/tensor/resize_impl.cu(525): error : calling a __host__ function("__floorf") from a __global__ function("onnxruntime::cuda::_ResizeCubicCoordinateMapping<int> ") is not allowed
```
The list of error goes on for other integral types like `unsigned char` as well as for function `roundf` at least
